uot;gem buffs&quot;</span><hr size=1> I admit to a lot of ignorance, as I'm only 43 and Tryll is my highest character on this or any server.  A little advice, please, from any higher level clerics and all those who benefit from their Symbol line of buffs:<br>
<br>
I use Symbol of Pinzarn nearly all the time on the tanks in my group; in dicey situations, I drop it on everyone in the group.  (My regular bunch hunts a lot in the Tower of Frozen Shadows lately, you can get a large rumble in there until you know the place well, which we are finally starting to do.)<br>
<br>
Now here comes level 44 and a Symbol that will cost me a boatload more to cast.  I'm not planning on using Naltron unless we're going against uber mobs (well uber for our level, all of us are 43/44 now cept our rogue barely 45), cause I think casting it a minimum of 6x a night with an outlay of 60+pp is too high for me to afford. Is that dumb logic?<br>
<br>
Question is, am I insane for using Pinzarn on a regular basis?  I think it's helped our group get through some bad situations with few(er) deaths.  Or, on the other hand, am I being stingy for saying I don't want to use Naltron except in exceptional cases cause it's expensive?<br>
<br>
I've been told by some clerics I know that they don't use any Symbol buffs except on dragon/planes raids.  Makes me feel either that I'm being stupid, wasteful, or a nervous Nellie over-buffing my party.<br>
<br>
I'd love any commentary/discussion you folks want to share.  I want to play my cleric best I can.  Thankee, all. <p>Tryllium Calaquendi<BR>
Cleric of Tunare, 43rd Circle<BR>
Proud member of <A href="http://pub44.ezboard.com/byeoldpub">Drunks of Tunare</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=xthorn>xthorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 332<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/2/01 2:38:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cleric &quot;gem buffs&quot;</span><hr size=1> My cleric almost never loots or borrows money from my other characters, but he still gets away buying many jaspers to buff tanks.  Don't use Naltron unless you're on a raid and are promised reimbursement.  Or give it to your melee friends who are soloing.   Jaspers are fairly cheap even with less than 100 charisma... personally I spend about 1/20th the money on symbols as I do on spells with my cleric (level 44 now). <p>-Xthorn, Power Ranger (55 Outrider of Karana)<BR>

<IMG SRC="http://www.people.fas.harvard.edu/~ccho/images/eqsig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhethral.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hethral</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/r Where's the corpse.</span><br>  Posts: 1108<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/2/01 12:31:23 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://the.truthbringers.com/Images/Members/HeadShots/HethralHead.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cleric &quot;gem buffs&quot;</span><hr size=1> Peridots will help you do your job better. You also have to balance how much mana you have with the manacost of spells, naltron carries a hefty mana cost with it.<br>
<br>
Typical situation with low blue con mobs:<br>
Main Tank: Reso/Hero, SoWords, Symbol of Pinzarn<br>
Enchanter: Reso/Hero, SoWords, Symbol of Pinzarn<br>
Secondary Tanks: Reso/Hero, AoFaith<br>
Everyone Else: Reso/Hero<br>
<br>
Typical situation with evenish con mobs:<br>
Main Tank: Reso/Hero, SoWords, Symbol of Naltron<br>
Enchanter: Reso/Hero, SoWords, Symbol of Naltron<br>
Secondary Tanks: Reso/Hero, SoWords, Symbol of Pinzarn<br>
Everyone Else: Reso/Hero, AoFaith<br>
<br>
Giving your main tank naltron helps alot once you get into places where things are double hitting for 100+ a hit, it also makes cheal much more efficient.  Your enchanter needs it for when mez gets broken or for mez resists, every lil bit you can give them makes them that much more likely to be alive after a fight.<br>
<br>
As for the cost of it. Most good groups will toss me some sort of gem/jewlery to sell to make up the difference. It's also where all the coin people give me for rez donations goes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usadara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sadara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 531<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/2/01 6:46:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cleric &quot;gem buffs&quot;</span><hr size=1> Naltron can become very expensive.  If you don't need to use it, don't cast it.  I don't cast my peridot using symbol all the time.  I will cast it all the time on the enchanters I group with.  For them, it's important to boost their AC and HP.  Enchanters can go down quicker than any class, that I've seen.<br>
<br>
If you want to keep your party buffed with Symbol, stick with Prinzarn.  I'm level 55 now and many of the clan are right around me in level.  For the most part, they get either no symbol or Prinzarn.  There are situations that I will cast Symbol of Mazrin (uses Peridot too) on the tanks.  But those situations are normally raids or places like Howling Stones where everything seems to Harm Touch.<br>
<br>
BTW, in the right raid situation you can easily burn through a few hundred plat in Peridots.  It's rare, but it's happened to me.  Don't be affraid to use Prinzarn.  Most people understand when you don't cast Naltron.  It costs to much.<br>
<br>
