 <p>Tryllium Calaquendi<BR>
Cleric of Tunare, 43rd Circle<BR>
Proud member of <A href="http://pub44.ezboard.com/byeoldpub">Drunks of Tunare</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udorfmedic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dorf Medic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 270<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/7/01 12:34:05 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.aardman.com/images/home/gilles.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cleric &quot;gem buffs&quot;</span><hr size=1> I typically carry 10 stacks of peridots 2 stacks of jaspers and one stack of pearls (Marzin/Pinzarn/Death Pact).  I know that this amounts to about 2200 plat in gems but it makes you as a cleric ready for most 12 hour camps or raids.  You may wonder that it may be extreme, but I feel that it is better to be prepared than to be out of gems (even if I give 6 stacks to the raid leader because they are not prepared.<br>
<br>
I make a point of telling the group that before loot splitting (assumes a masterlooter), all reagants for Clerics/Necros/Wizzies/Chanters and Paladins are adequately reimbursed.  If the group agrees then I buff according to their class.  You will find that often the tanks will help<br>
you by giving you some peridots or their gems to make sure that you dont fall short at the end of the day (or another day).<br>
<br>
It depends on what class but by enlarge I buff all members in my group with Marzin.  Some druids will prefer no gems but I still will give them a Pinzarn now that snare aggro seems out of whack.  Some enchanters will rune themselves, but very few necros and wizzies cast Manaskin.  Seems to boggle the mind, but they expect us clerics to buff them with our symbols while they wont put on their own 500 point damage (absorbing) shields.<br>
<br>
I typically spend 500 plat per nite replenishing my gem supply.  My charisma is 106 so I get the best value of 10.5 pp per peridot.  I would suggest that if you are buying gems in the quantities that I do, that you invest in some charisma items to raise your Charisma to 105+.  I will save you a lot over the long run.<br>
<br>
I have been carrying this many peridots on me since 49th level and it has always served me well.  I make a point of asking the evaccer to port me near a gem merchant (Inn 4 EC, Thurgadin, Kaladim (where my faction is high enough that will warrant the best gem prices).  If you make it a policy, people will respect you for it, they are happy to receive the best buffs and it doesn't really cost you anything.<br>
<br>
One last thing.  Please always make sure that the masterlooter covers your reagents BEFORE splitting the cash in the group.  I have had to teach some people that when you see (XXXX shares money with the group:  You receive 350 plat 300 gold, followed with the comment:'that should cover the gem cost right?'   Errr yes BUT every one else got 350 plat and 300 gold too without having to front the cost for the gems. <br>
<br>
Clerics, stick by your guns, have your group reimburse you for their extra 300-650 hp per buff, and you will find that as a group you will have a lot more fun.<br>
<br>
 <p>Khirsa Maelstorm 55 Vicar<BR>
Legion of Heroes<BR>
<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uresomatic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Res O Matic</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://donweebal.50megs.com/images/portrait.jpg BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/8/01 5:53:33 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://donweebal.50megs.com/images/portrait.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cleric &quot;gem buffs&quot;</span><hr size=1> Gonna have to go with Hethral on this one.  Noone in my groups really get Marzin/Naltron unless they get beat on an abnormal amount, such as rangers in a low taunt group or some such.  Since I hunt mainly in Sebilis, where Paladins, Warriors and SK's are readily available (sorry guys, <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), this hasn't been a problem.  The only thing I can tell you money wise is to take up a profitable trade skill to take up the slack.  I am a master brewer, and I make smithing tempers for my smithing friends for a tidy profit.  That is how I buy most of my peridots and jaspers and pearls.   <p><CENTER><img src="http://donweebal.50megs.com/images/domar-beta_black-final-half_sized.jpg"></CENTER>
