Proud member of <A href="http://pub44.ezboard.com/byeoldpub">Drunks of Tunare</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uarathena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arathena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dark Valkyrie of Innoruuk</span><br>  Posts: 361<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/10/01 11:21:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cleric &quot;gem buffs&quot;</span><hr size=1> Well, as a tank who can deliberately and intentionally build rogue-like levels of hate, I'd like to chime in with this: There is no such thing as being over buffed. You may have to pick them with a great deal of care, but you have them to be used. <br>
<br>
The key thing here, or at least it seems so to me, is to strike a balance in what you feel safe buffing with, what the group's individuals feel safe buffed with, and what your pocketbook can afford. That's going to be different with each regular group. I don't believe my cleric symbols anyone but the puller, namely me, because we're comfortable enough with each other's skills and abilities that no one else needs it. We can afford to symbol the whole party with the loot we're pulling, (Or so it seems...) but we don't see the need. Hero/Shield of words is more than enough for us. <br>
<br>
On the other hand, I know that there are definitely situations in which I will demand to be symboled with the cleric's very best, and will not move my little blue butt without it. This situations are almost entirely pulling situations, where I will be outside of the cleric's casting range for extended periods of time. I trust all players to be competant at their roles in a group until proven otherwise, and even when I'm the main tank, if the cleric feels he can keep up mana effeciency without symbol, or with a lesser symbol, then I'll trust him to do so and keep me alive. If I'm wrong, at least he can rez.. <br>
<br>
Basically, match your symbols to the situation... If your rogue seems to be having aggro problems, them by all means, Pinzarn him, or Naltron if he really seems to need it, there's not really any kind of formula to follow.  <p><center>Arathena Dracheseele<br>
